## Risks & Issues

### Current Risks

| Risk | Severity | Status | Mitigation |
|------|----------|--------|------------|
| Performance overhead from inheritance lookup | Medium | 📋 Design | Aggressive caching (5min TTL) |
| Cache invalidation complexity | Medium | 📋 Design | Clear invalidation rules, tests |
| Security: weak admin password | High | 📋 Design | Force password change on first login |
| Breaking existing code | High | ✅ Mitigated | Backward compatible, comprehensive tests |
| Schema validation performance | Low | ⏳ Not measured | Benchmark in implementation |

### Resolved Risks

| Risk | Resolution |
|------|------------|
| Breaking changes | ✅ All changes backward compatible |
| Learning curve | ✅ Comprehensive documentation provided |
| Repository abstraction leakage | ✅ Clean interfaces defined |
| Separate schema management complexity | ✅ Using file-based approach instead |

---

## Lessons Learned

### What Worked Well

1. **Incremental Approach** - Building layer by layer prevents overwhelm
2. **Documentation First** - Clear plan made implementation smooth
3. **No Breaking Changes** - Coexistence strategy works well
4. **JSON Schemas** - Declarative validation is powerful
5. **Design Before Code** - Special files design prevented premature implementation

### What Could Be Improved

1. **Tests Earlier** - Should write tests alongside code
2. **Examples Sooner** - Need more code examples upfront
3. **Benchmarks** - Should measure performance from start
4. **Pivot Quickly** - Recognized ContentSchema table approach was too complex, switched to file-based

